## 10. ARCHITECTURAL AND STRUCTURAL ANTI-PATTERNS

### 10.1 Monolithic File Structure

**Description:** AI generates large, monolithic files with tightly coupled components instead of modular architecture.

**Why AI does this:** Context window limitations mean AI works file-by-file. "AI coding agents never suggest refactoring." This leads to duplicated logic across files and inconsistent patterns.

**Impact:** Cognitive complexity scores of 20+ (recommended max: 15). Difficult to test, review, and maintain.

**Detection:** Cognitive complexity analysis. File length limits. Module coupling metrics.

**Sources:**
- [Understanding Anti-Patterns in AI-Generated Code](https://www.softwareseni.com/understanding-anti-patterns-and-quality-degradation-in-ai-generated-code/)

---

### 10.2 Excessive Comments

**Description:** AI generates inline comments for every line, increasing noise without adding value.

**Bad code:**
```typescript
// Get the user from the database
const user = await db.users.findOne({ id: userId });
// Check if the user exists
if (!user) {
  // Return a 404 error
  return res.status(404).json({ error: 'User not found' });
}
// Get the user's email
const email = user.email;
// Convert to lowercase
const normalizedEmail = email.toLowerCase();
```

**Good code:**
```typescript
const user = await db.users.findOne({ id: userId });
if (!user) {
  return res.status(404).json({ error: 'User not found' });
}
const normalizedEmail = user.email.toLowerCase();
```

**Why AI does this:** This is the #1 most common AI anti-pattern, occurring in 90-100% of generated code. AI is trained to be helpful and explanatory.

**Impact:** Cognitive overload. Comments become stale and misleading. Doubles file size for no value.

**Sources:**
- [Understanding Anti-Patterns in AI-Generated Code](https://www.softwareseni.com/understanding-anti-patterns-and-quality-degradation-in-ai-generated-code/)

---

### 10.3 Duplicated Logic Across Files (Context Blindness)

**Description:** AI generates the same utility function or business logic in multiple places because it cannot see the full codebase.

**Why AI does this:** Context window limitations. Copilot sees one file at a time. Even Cursor/Claude Code with 200K token contexts cannot see entire large codebases.

**Impact:** Inconsistent behavior when one copy is updated but others aren't. Maintenance burden.

**Detection:** Code duplication analysis (jscpd, SonarQube). File-level search for similar function names.

---

### 10.4 Missing Environment Validation

**Description:** AI uses environment variables without validation, causing cryptic runtime failures in deployment.

**Bad code:**
```typescript
const apiKey = process.env.API_KEY; // Could be undefined
const client = new ApiClient(apiKey); // Passes undefined
```

**Good code:**
```typescript
import { z } from 'zod';

const envSchema = z.object({
  API_KEY: z.string().min(1),
  DATABASE_URL: z.string().url(),
  NODE_ENV: z.enum(['development', 'production', 'test']),
});

const env = envSchema.parse(process.env);
// Now env.API_KEY is guaranteed to be a non-empty string
```

**Sources:**
- [Debugging AI-Generated Code](https://www.augmentcode.com/guides/debugging-ai-generated-code-8-failure-patterns-and-fixes)

